Finish the solution so that it sorts the passed in array of numbers. If the function passes in an empty array or null/nil value then it should return an empty array.

For example:

solution([1, 2, 10, 50, 5]); // should return [1,2,5,10,50]
solution(null); // should return []

//The examples and test cases give us the scenarios in which we would return an empty array so we set up the condition to return empty array based on those. 
//We can use the sort method to return the elements in ascending order.


function solution(nums){
  
  if (nums === [] || nums === null){
    return [];
  }
  
  return nums.sort((a, b) => a - b);
}
